{{Expand German|topic=culture|date=September 2011|Am dam des}} {{Infobox television | show_name =Am Dam Des | image = | caption = | camera = | runtime = | creator = | starring = | country =[[Austria]] | network = | first_aired ={{start date|1975|04|01}} | last_aired = | num_seasons = | num_episodes = | list_episodes = }}
'''''Am Dam Des''''' is a [[children's television series]] produced at the [[ORF (broadcaster)|ORF]] studios in [[Vienna]], [[Austria]] between 1975 and 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0486224/ |title=IMDB reference for ''AM Dam Des''}}</ref>
This live-action show was presented as 25-minute episodes, with an educational theme and different sections, hosted by {{Interlanguage link multi|Bernadette Schneider|de}}.<ref>{{cite news |title=Am Dam Des Sample Episode 1987 Youtube Video|url =https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=enJndfggA60&feature=relmfu |accessdate=November 20, 2011 | date=September 4, 1987}}</ref> She entertained children with poetry, stories, arts and crafts and various games. Bernadette had many recurring guests including Habakuk the Clown played by Arminio Rothstein, Mimi the Goose, a magician and Enrico the Clown played by Heinz Zuber.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0486224/fullcredits |title=IMDB Credits reference for ''Am Dam Des''}}</ref>
In 1977 [[Christoph Waltz]] joined the show as a singer.<ref>[http://www.nachrichten.at/nachrichten/kultur/Christoph-Waltz-vor-36-Jahren-Auftritt-bei-Am-dam-des;art16,1069710]</ref>
