{{Infobox Bilateral relations|Angola-Uruguay|Angola|Uruguay}}

'''Angola–Uruguay relations''' are the relations between [[Angola]] and [[Uruguay]]. The Angolan embassy in  [[Brasília]], [[Brasil]] is accredited to Uruguay.<ref>[http://www.embaixadadeangola.com.br/v2/ Angolan Embassy in Brasília] {{pt icon}}</ref> Uruguay has an embassy in [[Luanda]].<ref>[http://www.elpais.com.uy/informacion/gobierno-designo-embajadores-angola-emiratos.html Embassy of Uruguay in Luanda]</ref>

In 2003 both countries undersigned a technical, scientific, cultural and economical bilateral agreement.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parlamento.gub.uy/htmlstat/pl/acuerdos/acue18043.htm |title=Uruguay-Angola Agreement |date=20 October 2003 |publisher=[[Parliament of Uruguay]] |language=es |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141223033131/http://www.parlamento.gub.uy/htmlstat/pl/acuerdos/acue18043.htm |archivedate=23 December 2014 }}</ref> During the last decade, trade between both countries has been small but improving,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elobservador.com.uy/noticia/245643/angola-estrecho-vinculo-energetico-con-uruguay/ |title=Angola and Uruguay |date=12 March 2013 |publisher=[[El Observador (Uruguay)|El Observador]] |language=es}}</ref> with Uruguay buying petroleum and selling fish, rice, beef and other commodities to Angola.<ref>[http://www.uruguayxxi.gub.uy/exportaciones/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/09/Perfil-de-Angola-2013-Uruguay-XXI.pdf Angola-Uruguay trade] {{es icon}}</ref> There is a Uruguayan-African Chamber of Commerce, covering trade between Uruguay and different African countries.<ref>[http://www.camarauruguayoafricana.com/en/ Uruguayan-African Chamber of Commerce]</ref>

Both countries are members of the [[Group of 77]].

