The '''Association for Media Development in South Sudan''' ('''AMDISS''')  is a media association based in [[Juba]], [[South Sudan]] and was founded in 2003.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Interim assessment of media development in South Sudan: based on UNESCO's ...|last=|author=UNESCO|publisher=UNESCO Office Juba|year=2015|isbn=978-92-3-100092-8|location=Juba, South Sudan|pages=47}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npaid.org/Our-Work/Countries-we-work-in/Africa/South-Sudan/Development-cooperation-in-South-Sudan/Partners-for-development-cooperation-in-South-Sudan/Association-of-Media-Development-in-Sudan-AMDISS|title=Association of Media Development in Sudan (AMDISS)|last=|first=|date=|website=Norwegian People's Aid|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=9 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gurtong.net/ECM/Editorial/tabid/124/ctl/ArticleView/mid/519/articleId/21030/AMDISS-UJOSS-Are-Not-Media-Per-Se-Brother-Alier.aspx|title=AMDISS & UJOSS Are Not "Media" Per Se Brother Alier.|last=J Akol|first=Jacob|date=4 November 2017|website=Gurtong|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=9 February 2018}}</ref>

The group works to help strengthen the media and provide a framework in South Sudan to ensure freedom of speech, the right to information and other [[human rights]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npaid.org/Our-Work/Countries-we-work-in/Africa/South-Sudan/Development-cooperation-in-South-Sudan/Partners-for-development-cooperation-in-South-Sudan/Association-of-Media-Development-in-Sudan-AMDISS|title=Association of Media Development in Sudan (AMDISS)|last=|first=|date=|website=Norwegian people's Aid|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=9 February 2018}}</ref> and to protect freedom of expression; protect press freedom; and a system of self-regulation of media is in  place and effectively implemented and utilised in South Sudan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.norad.no/om-bistand/publikasjon/ngo-evaluations/2014/promotion-of-awareness-and-civil-society-support-for-freedom-of-expression-in-southern-sudan/|title=Promotion of Awareness and Civil Society Support for Freedom of Expression in Southern Sudan|last=Oscar|first=Lars|date=|website=Norad|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=9 February 2018}}</ref>

