[[file:St Ulrich Schwarzwald Kirche.jpg|thumb|Parish church in the village of St. Ulrich (former Benedictine priory)]]
'''Bollschweil Priory''' was a [[Cluniac]] monastery of [[nun]]s at [[Bollschweil]] (formerly ''Bolesweiler'') in the district of [[Breisgau-Hochschwarzwald]], [[Baden-Württemberg]], [[Germany]].

It was founded by Saint [[Ulrich of Zell]] in or after 1087 to complement the monastery he had founded for [[monk]]s at [[Grüningen Priory|Grüningen]], later moved to [[St. Ulrich's Priory in the Black Forest|Zell]]. The priory was moved to nearby Sölden in 1115, probably due to the unsuitability of the site, after which time the monastic community became known as [[Sölden Priory]].

