The '''Channel Islands Universities Consortium''' ('''CHUC''') was launched in September 1993. CHUC seeks to strengthen the relationship between the Bailiwicks of [[Guernsey]] and [[Jersey]], and It aims to promote the opportunities available within higher education to students from the islands. Its current members are [[University of Brighton]], [[Bournemouth University]], [[University of Plymouth]] and finally the [[University of Portsmouth]]  University representatives from CHUC visit the islands regularly to talk to interested students of both islands in groups and individually about the options available.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.careers.gg/14-19/Test.aspx |title=Guernsey Careers Service |publisher=Careers.gg |date= |accessdate=2012-10-08}}</ref>

