{{Politics of the European Union mini}} The '''Conference of Parliamentary Committees for Union Affairs of Parliaments of the European Union''' ('''COSAC''') is a conference of [[Member of the European Parliament|Members of the European Parliament]] (MEPs) and national [[Members of Parliament]] (MPs) who are drawn from [[parliament]]ary [[committee]]s responsible for [[European Union]] affairs.<ref name="Glossary">{{ cite web | publisher=[[Europa (web portal)|European Union website]] | title=Europa glossary: National parliaments | year=2008 | url=http://europa.eu/scadplus/glossary/national_parliaments_en.htm | accessdate=2008-05-27 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080408202445/http://europa.eu/scadplus/glossary/national_parliaments_en.htm | archivedate=2008-04-08 | df= }}</ref>
==History and role== [[File:COSAC Meeting Warsaw 2011.jpg|thumb|220px|left|COSAC meeting in [[Warsaw]] in 2011]] {{further|National parliaments of the European Union}} COSAC was founded in 1989 on a proposal of Laurent Fabius, then President of the French National Assembly and at the same time an MEP on the [[European Parliament Committee on Constitutional Affairs]] (AFCO). COSAC meets twice a year in the member state that holds the rotating [[Presidency of the Council of the European Union]].<ref name="Glossary"/>
The conference is mainly intended for personal contacts between Members of National Parliaments and [[Member of the European Parliament|MEP]]s, and for exchanges of information. The conference is therefore interested in the means by which the parliaments are able to co-operate and communicate with each other via interparliamentary meetings, and through the [[Interparliamentary EU Information Exchange|IPEX]] scrutiny website. The 17 Biannual COSAC report from April 2012 focused on recent developments in parliamentary scrutiny and the parliaments' use of IPEX.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cosac.eu/en/meetings/denmark2012/plenary/ |title=22-24 April 2012 Plenary Meeting |accessdate=8 June 2012 }}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
COSAC may also adopt contributions addressed to the [[List of European Union institutions|EU institutions]]. COSAC has gained the right to submit contributions and examine proposals on EU law relating to [[European Commissioner for Justice, Freedom & Security|Justice and Home Affairs]]<ref name="Glossary"/> and saw its role further expand under the [[Treaty of Lisbon]] with provisions for increased [[National parliaments of the European Union|involvement of national parliaments in EU affairs]].<ref name="TOL demo">{{ cite web | publisher=[[Europa (web portal)|European Union website]] | title=Treaty of Lisbon: A more democratic and transparent Europe | year=2008 | url=http://europa.eu/lisbon_treaty/glance/democracy/index_en.htm | accessdate=2008-05-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071229025748/http://europa.eu/lisbon_treaty/glance/democracy/index_en.htm | archive-date=2007-12-29 | dead-url=yes | df= }}</ref>
==Name== COSAC is a [[French language|French]] [[acronym]] for the conference's former name "'''C'''onférence des '''o'''rganes '''s'''pécialisés dans les '''a'''ffaires '''c'''ommunautaires et européennes des parlements de l'Union européenne" ('''Conference of Community and European Affairs Committees of Parliaments of the European Union'''). It is known by similar terms such as the Conference of European Community Affairs Committees<ref name="Glossary"/> and under the [[Treaty of Lisbon]] COSAC's name is listed as the '''conference of Parliamentary Committees for Union Affairs'''.<ref name="Lisbon protocol">{{ cite web |publisher=[[EUR-Lex|Eur-Lex website]] |title=Treaty of Lisbon: Protocol on the Role of National Parliaments in the European Union |year=2008 |url=http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:C:2007:306:0148:0150:EN:PDF |format=PDF |accessdate=2008-05-27 }}; [https://www.webcitation.org/6W3yc9H4N?url=http://europa.eu/rapid/midday-express.htm]</ref>
