The '''Integration and Development Centre for Information and Research''' or '''IDC''' ({{lang-uk|Інформаційно-дослідницький центр "Інтеграція та розвиток"}}, {{lang-ru|Информационно-исследовательский центр "Интеграция и развитие"}}) is a [[non-governmental organization]] from [[Simferopol]], Crimea, Ukraine, founded in 1997. It aims to promote civil society, democracy, tolerance and intercultural relations in [[Crimea]].

In 2009, the centre was chosen by an international jury led by the OSCE [[High Commissioner on National Minorities]] to receive the [[Max van der Stoel]] Award from the Ministry for Foreign Affairs of the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web |title=Max van der Stoel Award |url=https://www.osce.org/hcnm/mvdsaward |website=Osce.org |publisher=OSCE |accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref>

