[[File:Old Town Bridge Tower (8341896176).jpg|thumb|right|The tower in 2012]]
'''Old Town Bridge Tower''' ({{lang-cs|Staroměstská mostecká věž}}) is a [[Gothic architecture|gothic]] monument located in [[Prague]], Czech Republic. It was built in the late 14th century, during the rule of the Emperor [[Charles IV, Holy Roman Emperor|Charles IV]]. It was designed by the architect [[Petr Parléř]].

